benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/priceList - Retrieve priceList for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid Request paths tested with multiple scenarios resulting in HTTP 200 (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC16).
Empty data handling covered via TC04 (no data) and TC13 (empty database).
Query Parameters covered across multiple combinations and validations (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC05, TC07, TC11, TC12, TC19).
Error handling for invalid inputs and edge cases (TC05, TC07, TC10, TC19, TC22).
Service availability and dependency failure scenarios covered (TC09, TC20).
Performance/response time under load and retry scenarios (TC14, TC15, TC17).
Edge-case coverage for date boundaries and large data volumes (TC21, TC18).
Security tests for injection and XSS (TC10, TC22).
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested.
Caching behavior and headers (e.g., ETag, Cache-Control) are not tested.
Additional authorization scenarios (e.g., 403) not explicitly covered; only 401 tested.
Rate limiting/throttling tests are not covered.
UI accessibility (TC23) is not applicable to API; no API-side accessibility tests.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests for list responses when priceList data spans pages.
Add tests for caching headers and behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) on priceList responses.
Include tests for 403 Forbidden and other authorization edge cases.
Introduce rate limiting tests to validate throttling behavior under high load.
Clarify or remove UI accessibility TC23 or implement corresponding API-agnostic accessibility checks if UI is involved.
